- Dedcon: understands in-game alliance changes now and logs them
- Multiwinia encryption support removed, will only work with community versions now
- false game end detections no longer prevent you from continuing to play
- fixed file permissions on Windows install so regular users can edit the configuration
- more functionality if the metaserver is unreachable
- clients sending invalid acks are dropped
- ownership issues of objects get detected and published, they are likely to be cheats
- spectator login spam protection
- clients are now required to send sync values by default
- resetting all readiness states on territory selection, prevents fake starts
- territory change messages after game start are ignored
- new setting: ConnectionTimeout determines how long it takes for clients
  to be considered dropped
- Resyncs now work more reliably
- Dedcon: fixing automatic score recording if one of them is 0
- potentially harmful commands without TeamID 
  from out of sync clients are rejected
- Dedcon: score messages from isolated clients no longer end the game
- Dedcon: disabling JoinAs during recording for steam clients
